License Overview

This repository contains two kinds of material with different terms. The
authoritative per-file record is `ATTRIBUTIONS.csv`; the policy behind it is
`ASSET-LICENSING.md`. In short: CC BY 4.0, except where a file's
`ATTRIBUTIONS.csv` row says otherwise.

1. Original materials — CC BY 4.0

The repository's original materials authored by the maintainers are licensed
under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0) license.
This covers:

- all `.svg` files under `satellites/` and `other-spacecraft/` (colour
  illustrations and icons — original depictions, not traces);
- the raster renders of those SVGs (`*-512px.png`, `*-1024px.png`,
  regenerated with `tools/render_pngs.mjs`);
- documentation, tooling, and curation/metadata files (`index.json`,
  `ATTRIBUTIONS.csv`).

Full CC BY 4.0 text:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

Attribution requirement:
Please credit this project by linking to the repository:
https://github.com/eo-gos/satellite-visuals and retain notices of any
modifications where reasonable.

2. Sourced photographs and their cutouts — the upstream licence applies

Photograph files (`*-photo.*`) are third-party works committed only after
their owner's open licence is confirmed (public domain, CC BY, CC BY-SA,
CC BY-SA IGO, or an operator's published media terms). The maintainers do not
own these images and grant no rights in them; each file's licence, rights
holder, and source are recorded in its `ATTRIBUTIONS.csv` row, and that row —
not this file — states the terms under which you may reuse it.

Cutout derivatives (`*-photo-cut-*px.png`) are mechanical crops/background
removals of those photographs. The processing adds no new rights: each cutout
carries its source photograph's licence unchanged (share-alike terms included),
with the modification and tooling recorded in its own `ATTRIBUTIONS.csv` row.

Note that revisions of this repository before July 2026 contained rasters
resized from third-party websites without licence confirmation. Those files
were removed and are not licensed by this repository; any use of historical
revisions must comply with the original rights holders' terms.

Takedown / corrections:
If you are a rights holder and believe an asset is used in error, please open
an issue or contact the maintainer for removal or correction.
